  "body": "In 1.1, if you specify \"current-context: i-do-not-exist\" in a kubeconfig, and there's no matching context by that name in the contexts, kubelet silently uses what I assume is either an empty or a default configuration.\n\nThis can result in hilarity like wondering why your kubelet isn't using the TLS settings you provided, and spending several hours debugging the whole stack only to discover that you typo'd current-context :).\n\nIt would be better if kubelet and other users of kubeconfig.yaml errored out on such a misconfiguration, to make the failure obvious and trivial.\n",
